  "response_text": "Initially, mean green biomass values hover near 45,000 units but show slight fluctuations before entering a consistent downward phase, reaching a minimum of 42,057 units by year 27. Following this trough, biomass levels remain relatively stable with minor variations between years 27 and 32. A significant increase begins around year 33, characterized by a steady upward trend that accelerates notably after year 49. By year 100, biomass levels peak at approximately 60,535 units, marking a substantial recovery and growth compared to earlier years. The overall pattern indicates a transition from initial instability to a prolonged period of recovery and sustained increase in green biomass."
}

